comments: I had her for English 101 my first semester of college, over three years ago. I still remember her as the best English professor/teacher I\'ve ever had, and certainly one of the best professors I\'ve ever had. Three years later, and I thought I\'d do a review. I suppose that says something.
VERY GOOD TEACHER, INTELLIGENT, UNDERSTANDING. YOU DO THE WORK AND YOU\'LL HAVE TONS OF FUN IN HER CLASS.

Professor Jacobson knows what she is talking about. If you just do what she asks, you will excel. Homework matters in this class, so if you slack in this area, you will find yourself in trouble. She\'s not great with technology, so don\'t expect lots of videos. She will offer help outside of class, which really helps.
She is a great professor with a high energy level. She keeps you involved and is very helpful.
Really good professor, gets things done. Asks a lot from you, but involves herself completely. Organized, fun, interesting. Also hot.

I absolutely loved her! The class over all wasn\'t that fun, there were alot of essays to write one after the other. She puts her students first and is willing to do just about anything to help you. I really recommend her.
Over all a good teacher. She\'s upbeat and fun. She really cares about her students and puts in one on one time. She was also willing to help students outside of campus.
